{
  "texts": [
    "Query Decomposer.",
    "The two retrieval endpoints differ in their effective query formats (one targets keyword and the other semantic queries) and filtering of results based on the user's preferences for paper metadata (paper year, venue, field of study).",
    "In our query decomposition step, an LLM is prompted to re-format the user query into paraphrases appropriate for each endpoint, and to extract the user's requested settings for the metadata filters.",
    "We use the outputs of this step for retrieval.",
    "Search APIs."
  ]
}